@startuml
title Viaverse Dispute / Refund / Payout — Sequence Diagram

actor UserOrAdmin
participant "Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "dispute-service" as Dispute
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "payment-service" as Payment
participant "messaging-service" as Messaging
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka

UserOrAdmin -> Client : open dispute
Client -> BFF : POST /disputes
BFF -> Dispute : openDispute(command)
Dispute -> Marketplace : validate job participant/state
Marketplace --> Dispute : valid/invalid
Dispute -> Payment : block payout hold
Payment --> Dispute : payout blocked
Dispute -> Messaging : collect conversation refs
Dispute -> DB : insert DisputeCase + Evidence
Dispute -> Kafka : DisputeOpened

UserOrAdmin -> Client : resolve dispute
Client -> BFF : POST /admin/disputes/{id}/resolve
BFF -> Dispute : resolveDispute(command)
Dispute -> Payment : refund/release/split command
Payment -> DB : idempotent money movement state
Dispute -> DB : close dispute + audit log
Dispute -> Marketplace : update job dispute ref/status
Dispute -> Kafka : DisputeResolved
Dispute -> Kafka : RefundIssued / PayoutReleased

note bottom
Dispute service owns the case and resolution audit.
Payment service owns actual refund/payout movement and idempotency.
end note
@enduml
